This paper deals with motion segmentation, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of multiple models and clustering, which are common techniques in machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely category. The paper also deals with real-world effects such as strong perspectives and translations, which are common in robotics, making cs.RO (Robotics) a possible category. The paper also discusses performance evaluation, which is a common topic in multimedia, making cs.MM (Multimedia) another possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the limitations of the fundamental matrix approach, which is a common technique in linear algebra and optimization, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible category as well.
